This help you to find the vulnurability in the EC2 and Applications in it.
It assesses applications for exposure, vulnerabilities, and deviations from best practices
After performing an assessment, Amazon Inspector produces a detailed list of security findings that is organized by level of severity
For this to work properly you must install agent on the EC2 instances that are included in the assessment target
The target EC2 can be selected by Teg Key-Value pair attached to EC2s.
It provide pre-defined rules packages mapped to common security best practices and vulnerability definitions

You can also set to run the Inspector in certain prode. like run the rule in every 7 days.
and so it will do the automation of insoecting the running EC2 instances in every 7 day.
  - behind the scene it create a cron CW event with target of Inspector
